      <section id="solutions">
        <div class="section-inner">
          <div class="section-kicker">Solutions</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Three pilots, one shared platform.</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">
            GeoStash starts with three concrete products that share the same
            geo engine, security model and cloud architecture.
          </p>

          <div class="cards">
            <article class="card">
              <span class="badge">For real estate &amp; project teams</span>
              <h3>GeoStash Build – Project viewer</h3>
              <p>
                A clear map of all building projects in your area —
                from early plans to delivery.
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Interactive map of projects and sites</li>
                <li>Status: planned, in progress, completed</li>
                <li>Links to permits, drawings and reports</li>
                <li>Useful in talks with residents and partners</li>
              </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <span class="badge">For municipalities &amp; field teams</span>
              <h3>GeoStash Inspect – Clean-up &amp; inspection app</h3>
              <p>
                A light-weight inspection tool for the public space:
                capture issues once on site, follow them up centrally.
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Photo, category and GPS location per report</li>
                <li>Planning and follow-up in one dashboard</li>
                <li>Insight into hotspots and recurring issues</li>
                <li>Can connect to existing ticket systems</li>
              </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
              <span class="badge">For trails &amp; recreation</span>
              <h3>GeoStash Trail – Maps for families</h3>
              <p>
                Offline-friendly maps and routes focused on families
                with strollers – and later other accessibility profiles.
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Routes with gradient and surface information</li>
                <li>Offline access for use in the field</li>
                <li>Great for nature areas and holiday parks</li>
                <li>Built for accessible recreation projects</li>
              </ul>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

