      <section id="trust">
        <div class="section-inner">
          <div class="section-kicker">Trust</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Privacy-aware and ready to grow.</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">
            GeoStash is built with privacy, security and scalability in mind
            from the start. That makes it a good fit for public-sector use.
          </p>

          <div class="split">
            <div>
              <h3>Privacy by design</h3>
              <p>
                Each pilot starts with a sharp look at which data is actually
                required. Wherever possible we limit personal data and work with
                aggregated or anonymised information.
              </p>
              <div class="chip-list">
                <div class="chip">Data minimisation</div>
                <div class="chip">Clear retention rules</div>
                <div class="chip">Processor agreements</div>
                <div class="chip">Transparent registers</div>
              </div>

              <h3>Security</h3>
              <p>
                The platform uses encrypted connections, role-based access
                and separate environments for test, pilot and production.
              </p>
              <div class="chip-list">
                <div class="chip">HTTPS by default</div>
                <div class="chip">Role-based access</div>
                <div class="chip">Backups &amp; monitoring</div>
                <div class="chip">EU-hosted infrastructure</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div>
              <div class="callout">
                <strong>Early-stage, serious intent</strong><br /><br />
                GeoStash is currently in pilot mode. Together with partners we
                refine both the product and the legal/organisational side –
                such as DPIAs where needed and integration with your security
                policies. This page is not legal advice, but an invitation
                to co-create a future-proof geo solution.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

